url: https://github.com/tarun1219/SE_LLM_EVAL
abstract: >-
  A longitudinal empirical study comparing two generations of LLMs
  (2023: GPT-3.5-Turbo, LLaMA-2-7B; 2026: GPT-4o, Claude Sonnet 4-6,
  LLaMA-3.3-70B) as synthetic software-engineer survey respondents.
  We identify the "Kappa Paradox": RLHF-aligned 2026 models achieve
  better distributional similarity to human responses (lower chi-square)
  but collapse response diversity (Fleiss kappa ~0.48 vs human 0.10,
  mean Shannon entropy 0.45-0.50 bits vs human 1.86 bits). All results
  reproduce from archived model outputs without additional API calls.
keywords:
  - large language models
  - survey simulation
  - silicon sampling
  - RLHF
  - demographic diversity
  - Fleiss kappa
  - software engineering research
  - empirical study
